Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and
finely chop @shallot{1}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}.
Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @salt{}, @pepper{},
and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} (to taste). Roast for ~{7%minutes} (we'll add the
garlic bread then). (For 4 servings, leave green beans roasting and add garlic
bread to another baking sheet.)

Meanwhile, place @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and garlic in a
small, #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until softened, ~{10%seconds}. Spread
onto cut sides of demi-baguette; season with salt and pepper. Once green beans
have roasted 7 minutes, toss and push to one side of sheet. Add garlic bread
to empty side, cut sides up. Bake until green beans are tender and bread is
toasted, ~{5-7%minutes}. (For 4, roast green beans on top rack and bread on
middle rack.)

Pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and
pepper. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.
Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside to rest.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add shallot and cook,
stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and
@water{1/4%cup} (⅓ cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook, scraping up
any browned bits from bottom of pan, until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn
off heat; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide steak, green beans, and garlic bread between plates. Top steak with sauce.
Sprinkle green beans with additional chili flakes, if you like.